            <h3>HoS Reborn for WoW!</h3>
            <a href=users.php?action=view&user_id=3>Sepa</a> writes "From Koikeeper&#39;s post:<br><br> Welcome friends.<br><br>After nearly two years of hiatus, i am returning to virtual<br>life. Through all this time, i have missed you all terribly.<br>Through a few people, i have been able to keep tabs on the<br>comings and goings.<br><br>After speaking with friends, I have decided to return to<br>gaming. We intend to create a new guild in Worlds of<br>Warcraft. The logic is thus: We want something new, and EQII<br>isn&#39;t enough. We want a game that won&#39;t force us all to buy<br>new computers.<br><br>We will be creating a guild in WoW. It is our intention to<br>use the same name, Harmony of Souls.<br><br>A few broad strokes....<br><br>Leave the baggage in EQ. We are starting fresh.<br><br>We are NOT going to go hardcore. We want to have fun. Casual<br>fun. Remember how that was?<br><br>We may evolve into raiding, but it took us over two years to<br>get there the first time, so there is no reason to worry<br>about it now.<br><br>The guild will be modeled after the original missions of<br>HoS: there was a time when HoS members were thought of as<br>the cavalry for those in need, and the peacekeepers of the<br>server. We had an amazing reputation. I would like to<br>recapture that spirit.<br><br>FInally, if you don&#39;t want to do this- don&#39;t. There will be<br>no pressure to join, or take up the banner again. We are<br>looking to rekindle friendships, not recapture some lost<br>childhood.<br><br>I look forward to this. See you soon. " 
